----------------------------------------------------

VIRA-AI MODULAR BACKEND - PRODUCTION ENVIRONMENT SETTINGS

----------------------------------------------------

IMPORTANT: Values must be replaced by the CI/CD pipeline or Secrets Manager in a real production environment.

Leaving values empty here forces the deployment process to fail if secrets are not properly injected.

--- 1. GENERAL APPLICATION SETTINGS ---

APP_ENV="production"

The PORT is usually determined by the hosting service (e.g., 8080 or 8000)

PORT=8000

SECRET KEY: MUST be filled by the deployment service using a secure secret manager.

SECRET_KEY=""

--- 2. DATABASE CONFIGURATION (PostgreSQL Example) ---

Database credentials must be injected at runtime.

DB_HOST=""
DB_PORT=""
DB_NAME=""
DB_USER=""
DB_PASSWORD=""
DATABASE_URL=""

--- 3. SECURITY & AUTHENTICATION (JWT) ---

JWT_ALGORITHM="HS256"
ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES=30
REFRESH_TOKEN_EXPIRE_DAYS=7

--- 4. THIRD-PARTY API KEYS ---

OPENAI_API_KEY=""

HUGGINGFACE_API_KEY=""

--- 5. LOGGING SETTINGS ---

LOG_LEVEL="INFO"
